The paper focuses on lossy compression techniques for N-body simulations, which involve large-scale data processing and storage. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes novel optimization techniques for compression, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The experiments involve running simulations on a supercomputer, which suggests the category of cs.SC (Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between compression rate and ratio, which is related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed methods compared to state-of-the-art compressors, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
